#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:5.1"
msgid "20. Kayavikkayasikkhāpada"
msgstr "20. The training rule on bartering"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:6.1"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.241"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.109"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.20.1"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2238"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:6.2"
msgid "Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:6.3"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā upanando sakyaputto paṭṭo hoti cīvarakammaṃ kātuṃ."
msgstr "At that time Venerable Upananda the Sakyan had become skilled at making robes."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:6.4"
msgid "So paṭapilotikānaṃ saṅghāṭiṃ karitvā surattaṃ suparikammakataṃ katvā pārupi."
msgstr "He made an outer robe of rags, well-dyed and beautifully executed, and he wore it."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:6.5"
msgid "Atha kho aññataro paribbājako mahagghaṃ paṭaṃ pārupitvā yenāyasmā upanando sakyaputto tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "Just then a certain wanderer who was wearing an an expensive robe approached Upananda"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:6.6"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ upanandaṃ sakyaputtaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "and said,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:6.7"
msgid "“sundarā kho tyāyaṃ, āvuso, saṅghāṭi;"
msgstr "“Your outer robe is beautiful."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:6.8"
msgid "dehi me paṭenā”ti."
msgstr "Please give it to me in exchange for my robe.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:6.9"
msgid "“Jānāhi, āvuso”ti."
msgstr "“But do you know what you’re doing?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:6.10"
msgid "“Āmāvuso, jānāmī”ti."
msgstr "“I do.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:6.11"
msgid "“Handāvuso”ti,"
msgstr "“Ok then,”"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:6.12"
msgid "adāsi."
msgstr "and he gave it."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:6.13"
msgid "Atha kho so paribbājako taṃ saṅghāṭiṃ pārupitvā paribbājakārāmaṃ agamāsi."
msgstr "The wanderer put on the outer robe and went to the wanderers’ monastery."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.110"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:6.14"
msgid "Paribbājakā taṃ paribbājakaṃ etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr "And the wanderers said to him,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:6.15"
msgid "“sundarā kho tyāyaṃ, āvuso, saṅghāṭi;"
msgstr "“This outer robe of yours is beautiful."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:6.16"
msgid "kuto tayā laddhā”ti?"
msgstr "How did you get it?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:6.17"
msgid "“Tena me, āvuso, paṭena parivattitā”ti."
msgstr "“I got it in exchange for my robe.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:6.18"
msgid "“Katihipi tyāyaṃ, āvuso, saṅghāṭi bhavissati,"
msgstr "“But how long will this outer robe last you?"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:6.19"
msgid "soyeva te paṭo varo”ti."
msgstr "That robe of yours was better.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2239"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:7.1"
msgid "Atha kho so paribbājako—“saccaṃ kho paribbājakā āhaṃsu—‘katihipi myāyaṃ saṅghāṭi bhavissati. Soyeva me paṭo varo’”ti"
msgstr "The wanderer realized they were right,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:7.2"
msgid "yenāyasmā upanando sakyaputto tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "and so he returned to Upananda"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:7.3"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ upanandaṃ sakyaputtaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "and said,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:7.4"
msgid "“handa te, āvuso, saṅghāṭi;"
msgstr "“Here’s your outer robe;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:7.5"
msgid "dehi me paṭan”ti."
msgstr "give me back my robe.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:7.6"
msgid "“Nanu tvaṃ, āvuso, mayā vutto—"
msgstr "“But didn’t I ask you"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:7.7"
msgid "‘jānāhi, āvuso’ti."
msgstr "if you knew what you were doing?"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:7.8"
msgid "Nāhaṃ dassāmī”ti."
msgstr "I won’t give it back.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:7.9"
msgid "Atha kho so paribbājako ujjhāyati khiyyati vipāceti—"
msgstr "Then that wanderer grumbled and complained,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:7.10"
msgid "“gihīpi naṃ gihissa vippaṭisārissa denti,"
msgstr "“Even householders give things back to a householder who has regrets."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:7.11"
msgid "kiṃ pana pabbajito pabbajitassa na dassatī”ti."
msgstr "How then can an ascetic not give back to another ascetic?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2240"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:8.1"
msgid "Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tassa paribbājakassa ujjhāyantassa khiyyantassa vipācentassa."
msgstr "Monks heard the complaints of that wanderer,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:8.2"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "and the monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:8.3"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized Upananda,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:8.4"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma āyasmā upanando sakyaputto paribbājakena saddhiṃ kayavikkayaṃ samāpajjissatī”ti."
msgstr "“How can Venerable Upananda barter with a wanderer?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="4"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2241"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:9.1"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū āyasmantaṃ upanandaṃ sakyaputtaṃ anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "After criticizing him in many ways, they informed the Master. …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:9.2"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, upananda, paribbājakena saddhiṃ kayavikkayaṃ samāpajjasī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, Upananda, that you did this?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:9.3"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:9.4"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked him: “…"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:9.5"
msgid "kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, paribbājakena saddhiṃ kayavikkayaṃ samāpajjissasi."
msgstr "Foolish man, how can you barter with a wanderer?"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:9.6"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.111"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:9.7"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:10.1"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2242"></a>
#. <strong class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:10.2"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhu nānappakārakaṃ kayavikkayaṃ samāpajjeyya, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "‘If a monk barters in various ways, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.’”"

#. </strong> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:10.3"
msgid "(<em>20</em>:<strong>39</strong>)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:11.1"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.20.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2243"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:11.2"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr "A:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:11.3"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "whoever …"

#. </span><strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:11.4"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "Monk:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:11.5"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr "… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order through a formal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is unchallengeable and fit to stand—"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:11.6"
msgid "ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2244"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:12.1"
msgid "Nānappakārakaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Various ways:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:12.2"
msgid "cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārā, antamaso cuṇṇapiṇḍopi dantakaṭṭhampi dasikasuttampi."
msgstr "robes, almsfood, dwellings, or medicines; even bath powder, a toothbrush, or a piece of thread."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.242"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2245"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:13.1"
msgid "Kayavikkayaṃ samāpajjeyyāti"
msgstr "Barters:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:13.2"
msgid "iminā imaṃ dehi, iminā imaṃ āhara, iminā imaṃ parivattehi, iminā imaṃ cetāpehīti."
msgstr "if he misbehaves, saying, “Give that for this/bring that for this/purchase that with this/exchange that for this,”"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:13.3"
msgid "Ajjhācarati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:13.4"
msgid "Yato kayitañca hoti vikkayitañca attano bhaṇḍaṃ parahatthagataṃ parabhaṇḍaṃ attano hatthagataṃ, nissaggiyaṃ hoti."
msgstr "When it has been bartered—his own goods are in the hands of the other and the other’s goods are in his own hands—it becomes subject to relinquishment."

#. </span></p><hr><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:13.5"
msgid "Nissajjitabbaṃ saṃghassa vā gaṇassa vā puggalassa vā."
msgstr "The goods should be relinquished to an Order, a group, or an individual."

#. <span class="kamma"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:13.6"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, nissajjitabbaṃ …"
msgstr "“And, monks, it should be relinquished in this way. …"

#. <span class="add"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:13.7"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr "To be expanded as in <a href=\"/en/pi-tv-bu-vb-np1#13\">Relinquishment 1, paragraphs 13–17</a>, with appropriate substitutions. …"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:13.8"
msgid "“ahaṃ, bhante, nānappakārakaṃ kayavikkayaṃ samāpajjiṃ."
msgstr "‘Venerables, I have bartered in various ways."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:13.9"
msgid "Idaṃ me nissaggiyaṃ."
msgstr "This is to be relinquished."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:13.10"
msgid "Imāhaṃ saṃghassa nissajjāmī”ti … pe …"
msgstr "I relinquish it to the Order.’ …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:13.11"
msgid "dadeyyāti … pe …"
msgstr "the Order should give …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:13.12"
msgid "dadeyyunti … pe …"
msgstr "you should give …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:13.13"
msgid "āyasmato dammīti."
msgstr "‘I give this back to you.’”"

#. </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:14.1"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:14.2"
msgid "Kayavikkaye kayavikkayasaññī, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If it is bartering, and he perceives it as bartering, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:14.3"
msgid "Kayavikkaye vematiko, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If it is bartering, but he is unsure if it is, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:14.4"
msgid "Kayavikkaye nakayavikkayasaññī, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If it is bartering, but he does not perceive it as bartering, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="10"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2247"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.112"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:15.1"
msgid "Nakayavikkaye kayavikkayasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If it is not bartering, but he perceives it as bartering, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:15.2"
msgid "Nakayavikkaye vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If it is not bartering, but he is unsure if it is, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:15.3"
msgid "Nakayavikkaye nakayavikkayasaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr "If it is not bartering, and he does not perceive it as bartering, there is no offense."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:16.1"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="11"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2248"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:16.2"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:16.3"
msgid "agghaṃ pucchati,"
msgstr "if he asks for the price;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:16.4"
msgid "kappiyakārakassa ācikkhati,"
msgstr "if he tells an attendant;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:16.5"
msgid "“idaṃ amhākaṃ atthi, amhākañca iminā ca iminā ca attho”ti bhaṇati,"
msgstr "if he says, “I have this and I have need of such-and-such;”"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:16.6"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:16.7"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. </p><hr><p class="endsutta"><a class="sc" id="12"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2249"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:17.1"
msgid "Kayavikkayasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dasamaṃ."
msgstr "The tenth rule, the training rule on bartering, is finished."

#. </p><p class="endchapter"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:17.2"
msgid "Kosiyavaggo dutiyo."
msgstr "The second chapter on silk is finished."

#. </p><p class="endsection summary"><a class="sc" id="13"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2250"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:18.1"
msgid "Tassuddānaṃ"
msgstr "This is the summary:"

#. </p><p class="uddana"><a class="sc" id="14"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2251"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:19.1"
msgid "Kosiyā suddhadvebhāgā,"
msgstr "Silk, entirely, two parts,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:19.2"
msgid "chabbassāni nisīdanaṃ;"
msgstr "Six years, sitting-mat;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:19.3"
msgid "Dve ca lomāni uggaṇhe,"
msgstr "And two on wool, should take,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np20:19.4"
msgid "ubho nānappakārakāti."
msgstr "Two on various kinds."

